The paper discusses the comparison between peer review and bibliometrics in predicting the scholarly impact of scientific publications. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the study focuses on the evaluation of research outputs, we believe that cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.CR, and cs.SI.
